There is no reference in this satire which fixes the date precisely, and we are obliged to fall back upon general indications. The criticisms to which it is a reply were called forth by the sensational and persona] tone of the early seventh and eighth satireS, and especially of the second, in particular, vss. 91 ff. show that this was written after the second and, probably, very soon after it. Maecenas is not mentioned in 'this satire, as he is not referred to in the other earlier ones, though a personal mention would have been natural in 8,8 and 14. Nor is there
